---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Upload
permalink: "upload/"
---
<section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
  <!-- Page Title -->
  <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
    <!-- Optional: upload icon (SVG) -->
    <svg
      class="h-6 w-6 text-gray-700 mr-2"
      xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
      fill="none"
      viewBox="0 0 24 24"
      stroke="currentColor"
    >
      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"
        d="M4 16v1a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2v-1M12 12v8m0-8l-3 3m3-3l3 3m-3-10v8" />
    </svg>
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800">File Upload</h1>
  </div>

  <!-- Yellow Warning Box -->
  <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 p-4 mb-6">
    <div class="flex items-start">
      <svg
        class="h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 text-yellow-500 mr-2"
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        fill="currentColor"
        viewBox="0 0 20 20"
      >
        <path
          fill-rule="evenodd"
          d="M8.257 3.099c.765-1.36 2.682-1.36 3.447 0l5.516 9.82c.75 1.335-.213
                 2.98-1.724 2.98H4.465c-1.51 0-2.475-1.645-1.724-2.98l5.516-9.82zM11 
                 13a1 1 0 10-2 0 1 1 0 002 0zm-1-2a1 1 0 01-1-1V7a1 1 0 
                 112 0v3a1 1 0 01-1 1z"
          clip-rule="evenodd"
        />
      </svg>
      <p class="text-sm text-yellow-800">
        There is nothing that needs to be uploaded here unless you have had a 
        <strong>Qualifying Event</strong>. A Qualifying Event is marriage, divorce, 
        death, birth/adoption of a child, loss of coverage, etc. You would need to 
        upload proof of the Qualifying Event. In addition to uploading the documents, 
        you will need to send an email to 
        <a 
          href="mailto:benadmin@tri-starsystems.com" 
          class="underline text-yellow-900 hover:text-yellow-800"
        >
          benadmin@tri-starsystems.com
        </a>
        to let them know about the Qualifying Event.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Blue Info Box -->
  <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-400 p-4 mb-8">
    <div class="flex items-start">
      <svg
        class="h-5 w-5 flex-shrink-0 text-blue-500 mr-2"
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        fill="currentColor"
        viewBox="0 0 20 20"
      >
        <path
          fill-rule="evenodd"
          d="M18 10c0 4.418-3.582 8-8 8s-8-3.582-8-8 
             3.582-8 8-8 8 3.582 8 8zm-9-4a1 1 0 112 
             0v2a1 1 0 11-2 0V6zm.25 4.25a.75.75 0 10-
             1.5 0v3.5a.75.75 0 101.5 0v-3.5z"
          clip-rule="evenodd"
        />
      </svg>
      <p class="text-sm text-blue-800">
        <strong>Note:</strong> We will only accept the following file formats (extensions) 
        for files up to 3 MB in size: <br />
        <span class="font-medium">.JPG  .TIF  .GIF  .PDF  .DOC  .DOCX  .XLS  .XLSX  .CSV</span> 
        – <span class="font-semibold">Do NOT upload .zip files or password-protected files.</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Instructions List -->
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-4 mb-8 text-gray-700">
    <li>
      <span class="font-medium">All pages to one file on your computer</span><br />
      Save all supporting documentation to one file, if possible.
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="font-medium">Optional Comments</span><br />
      If you wish to add an optional comment, <strong>please upload only 1 file</strong>, 
      the file associated with the comment. Otherwise, the comment will be associated 
      with the first file received. You’ll be able to upload more documents, thereafter.
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="font-medium">Select the file to upload to Tri‐Star</span><br />
      Click the <strong>Choose File</strong> or <strong>Browse</strong> button below and select 
      the file you saved.
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="font-medium">Upload the file to Tri‐Star</span><br />
      Click the <strong>Upload</strong> button below to securely transfer your file to us.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <!-- Comments Textarea -->
  <div class="mb-6">
    <label for="comments" class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">
      Comments (Optional)
    </label>
    <textarea
      id="comments"
      name="comments"
      rows="4"
      class="mt-1 block w-full rounded-md border-gray-300 shadow-sm 
             focus:border-blue-500 focus:ring-blue-500 sm:text-sm"
      placeholder="Optional comments"
    ></textarea>
  </div>

  <!-- File Input & Buttons -->
  <form action="/upload" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
    <div class="mb-6">
      <label for="file-upload" class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">
        Select file to upload:
      </label>
      <input
        id="file-upload"
        name="file"
        type="file"
        accept=".jpg,.tif,.gif,.pdf,.doc,.docx,.xls,.xlsx,.csv"
        class="block w-full text-sm text-gray-700
               file:mr-4 file:py-2 file:px-4
               file:rounded-md file:border-0
               file:text-sm file:font-semibold
               file:bg-blue-50 file:text-blue-700
               hover:file:bg-blue-100"
        required
      />
    </div>

    <div class="flex justify-end space-x-2">
      <button
        type="button"
        onclick="window.history.back()"
        class="btn btn-cancel"
      >
        Cancel
      </button>
      <button
        type="submit"
        class="btn btn-submit"
      >
        Upload
      </button>
    </div>
  </form>
</section>
